# React Native Standards (Expo SDK 55)

## SDK Version Matrix

| Component | Version |
|---|---|
| Expo SDK | 55 |
| React | 19.2.0 |
| React Native | 0.83.2 |
| Android Target API | 36 |
| New Architecture | Mandatory (cannot be disabled) |

## SDK 55 Specifics

- New Architecture is mandatory — all code must be New Arch compatible
- Reanimated v4 — `react-native-reanimated/plugin` must be LAST in babel plugins; do NOT add `react-native-worklets/plugin` separately (bundled inside reanimated)
- Audio → `expo-audio` only (`createAudioPlayer`, `useAudioPlayer`, `setAudioModeAsync`). `expo-av` is deprecated
- Notifications → always pass `projectId` to `getExpoPushTokenAsync()` via `Constants.expoConfig?.extra?.eas?.projectId`
- Edge-to-edge mandatory on Android — use `react-native-safe-area-context`
- File system → use `expo-file-system/next` API, avoid legacy patterns
- Do NOT add `newArchEnabled` or `edgeToEdgeEnabled` to `app.json` — both are mandatory defaults

## API Calls — Use `fetchAPI` (MANDATORY)

All HTTP requests MUST use `fetchAPI` from `@/lib/fetch`. Never raw `fetch()`.

Provides: auto JWT injection, 401 token refresh, retry logic, centralized error handling.

```tsx
// ❌ raw fetch — no auth, no retry
const res = await fetch(`${API_URL}/ride/history`);

// ✅ fetchAPI
import { fetchAPI } from "@/lib/fetch";
const { data } = await fetchAPI("/(api)/ride/history");
```

## Component Patterns

- Named exports with typed props interfaces
- NativeWind (Tailwind) for styling
- Platform-specific code via `Platform.select`
- Handle keyboard avoiding views
- Pull-to-refresh on lists
- Loading + error states on all async screens
- FlatList: use `getItemLayout` for fixed-height items
- Icons: `<Image source={icons.xxx} />` with PNG from `constants/index.ts`
- Immutable state updates: `setUser(prev => ({ ...prev, name }))` — never mutate directly

## Dependencies

- Install with `npx expo install <pkg>` — NEVER `npm install` for Expo packages
- All Expo packages MUST use `^55.x` or `~55.x` versioning
- Check `bundledNativeModules.json` for pinned versions before adding native libs
- Keep `reanimated`, `screens`, `gesture-handler`, `safe-area-context` at bundled versions
- Prefer New Architecture-compatible libraries (Fabric / TurboModules)
- Run `npx expo-doctor@latest` after any dependency change
- Driver and passenger apps MUST share identical versions for common packages
- Lock files (`package-lock.json`) MUST be committed

## Android Build

- `expo-build-properties` plugin manages `compileSdkVersion`, `targetSdkVersion`, `minSdkVersion`
- Target API 36+ for Play Store compliance
- EAS CLI >= 18.0.0
- `eas update` requires `--environment` flag
